author: gstein
msg: Continued SWIG work. This change focuses on building and linking the
Python wrappers into a usable state. With this, I was able to open an
FS repository and query data from it.
This change introduces a new "libsvn_swig_py" library to hold utility
functions for the Python wrappers. We'll add libsvn_swig_perl, etc as
those bindings are built.
* gen-make.py: generate custom build instructions for the new
"swig-py" type.
* build.conf: add more 'libs' dependencies for all of our
libraries. these dependencies will then go into the libraries
themselves so they can be dynamically loaded with all necessary
dependencies.
(libsvn_swig_py): define new library; used for helper functions for
the SWIG python wrappers.
* configure.in: add new constructs for finding SWIG and deciding which
language bindings to build.
* Makefile.in: add config/build information for the "swig-py" type
* ac-helpers/get-py-info.py: new file used to figure out where Python
keeps its headers.
* include/svn_fs.h: (svn_fs_warning_callback_t) disable the warning
callback type; SWIG doesn't like varargs functions.
(svn_fs_dir_entries): change the name of the argument so that SWIG
can differentiate it from the functions which return property hash
tables.
* bindings/swig/svn_ra.i: add typemaps.i for its types/utility funcs
* bindings/swig/svn_types.i (MAKE_TYPE): new macro for forcing a type
to appear in the output wrappers file.
(python,except typemap): fix exception function typo
* bindings/swig/util.i: wrap apr_initialize and apr_terminate. add
some more includes into the output wrapper file.
* bindings/swig/svn_fs.i: disable constructor/destructor generation.
(char*** typemap): update function name for the C string to
Python list utility.
(entries_p typemap): handle the output of svn_fs_dir_entries()
use MAKE_TYPE/MAKE_TYPE_IMPL to force SWIGTYPE_p_svn_stream_t and
SWIGTYPE_p_svn_txdelta_stream_t symbols into the wrapper.
(c_strings_to_list): moved to new swigutil.c file for the
libsvn_swig_py library.
* bindings/swig/setup.py: build _fs, _repos, and _util wrappers (the
others don't compile yet). add the appropriate libs, including the
new libsvn_swig_py, and SWIG's libswigpy.
* bindings/swig/apr.i (apr_size_t 'in' typemap): fix the typemap to
prevent type conflicts between (old) "unsigned long *" and
"apr_size_t *"
(apr_hash_t** 'ignore' typemap): create generic version for any
function that returns a hash table.
(PROPHASH typemaps): use new svn_swig_prophash_to_dict() utility
function and the new hash OUTPUT typemap.
(prophash_to_dict): moved to swigutil.c
* bindings/swig/svn_client.i: use new svn_swig_prophash_to_dict()
(statushash typemap): use new svn_swig_convert_hash util func.
* bindings/swig/swigutil.c: new file to implement utility functions
for all the SWIG wrappers (each wrapper and each language). this
gets built and installed.
* bindings/swig/swigutil.h: prototype the helper functions in
swigutil.c. define some SWIG types, funcs when needed.
